This establishment could have received a better rating had it not been for a nasty and avoidable altercation that my wife and I were involved in with the staff a few weeks back. But more on that after my review of the food and staff. First off, the food is pretty good and borderline great if you decide to dine in or take out around midday when the food is constantly being churned out. Although that may sound like a negative connotation it's not. The food is fresh and delicious and has that authentic Dominican touch many other nearby establishments lack. Their selection of dishes vary on a daily basis and are reasonably priced. Do try and make it before nightfall as the food stops being freshly prepared after a certain hour. I would say sometime after 6pm or 7pm. I say this due to the less than stellar meals I've experienced after these hours.  Now on to the staff.  The servers are mainly ladies of Dominican descent and do speak a broken english that can still be understood. The business seems family run since a lot of the staff look alike and share similar characteristics and physical features. Now I can empathize with restaurant workers and their long hours and the plethora of unruly customers they must deal with on a constant and daily basis but professionalism must still be a standard maintained in any business and these ladies unfortunately wear their emotions on their sleeves. Depending on which day you catch them, you may get a greeting with great service. On the off chance that you catch them on a bad day, you might get the worst service ever. Also, some word of advice. This establishment is affiliated with UberEats and Grubhub. So expect a longer than usual delivery time if you place an order over the phone. Any upwards of 40 to 60 minutes plus. Now on to my altercation. Long story short, my wife and two young daughters stopped off to grab some late dinner. It was around 8pm and unbeknownst to us, this establishment turns into a drunken hangout spot for local workers and friends of the family, I assume. One of the servers got my wife's order wrong and was nasty towards my wife when she brought it to her attention.  A shouting match ensued and one of the drunken patrons that claimed to be a delivery boy approached my wife and demanded that she leave the premises. He yelled obscenities at my wife and kids and were ushered out by some other gentleman that claimed to be the owner. When my wife informed me of what had transpired I went to the establishment to demand an explanation from the owner. When I arrived he was no where to be found and I was immediately confronted by a group of drunk men that claimed they ran the business and that if I had any problems "we could step outside and work them out". By his body language and tone I got the message and expressed my disdain and disgust with the service and his actions as I walked out the door. Almost immediately a gentlemen ran out behind me and apologized for what had taken place. The gentleman didn't offer a refund or an explanation for who the men that confronted my wife and I were. Needless to say I avoided a potential painful beatdown all on account of a wrong order. So take your chances if you will with this place. The food is good but potentially bad for your physical health. Depending on which time of the day you intend to visit. Smh.

This restaurant has proven that they're unprofessional. In sending my food (bacon, scrambled eggs, French toast) the resturant did not provide utensils, napkins, syrup, nor butter. In my order I was resulted to eating my food at work with my hands (I was hungry and pregnant). In calling numerous times the staff as well as the manager stated they did not know what could be done. The manager then pass off the phone to another staff member. Once again, I explain to the staff that I did not recieve any utensils, napkins, syrup, nor butter. The staff memeber male said they will send someone out in 5mins. After 30mins past I reach out to Grub Hub in which they tried to reach out to the restaurant numerous times as well as but the restaurant did not pick up the phone. I called the resturant myself to request a full refund. The resturant manager (female) stated they will give me a full refund but I would have to contact Grub Hub. I called Grub Hub back  and informed them of what the resturant stated. When Grub Hub contacted the resturant, the manager changed the refund to 20% instead of full refund value. This is very unprofessional and in calling the resturant back will just be pointless at this moment. Please becareful before order from this location.

I ordered off of grub hub. The estimated delivery time was between 2:15 and 2:25, it arrived at 2:48. I got a salmon Caesar salad and soursop juice. I asked for extra dressing which I did not receive. I received no cutlery or straw. There was so much additional liquid at the bottom of my salad that I had to pour it out before attempting to eat it. My salmon was under seasoned, over cooked and almost ice cold. When finally delivered, they did not get out of the car so I had to walk all the way out to the car in order to receive my food instead of coming to the door. The lettuce in my salad was wilted. The croutons were soggy. The soursop juice was pretty good though, hence the single star. I will not be ordering from this place again. I’m upset that I even left a tip.
